<subSubSection box="[151,550,541,568]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,550,541,568]" box="[151,550,541,568]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,550,541,568]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,550,541,568]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Whitley, 1945" authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1945" box="[238,550,541,568]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Moolgarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,372,541,568]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Moolgarda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Whitley, G. P." box="[379,550,541,567]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref13893" refString="Whitley, G. P. (1945) New sharks and fishes from Western Australia Part 2. Australian Zoologist, 11 (1), 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="1945">Whitley, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="137" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,608,923]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,608,634]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Whitley, G. P." box="[275,447,608,635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref13893" refString="Whitley, G. P. (1945) New sharks and fishes from Western Australia Part 2. Australian Zoologist, 11 (1), 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="1945">Whitley (1945)</bibRefCitation>
described the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1945" box="[685,810,608,634]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Moolgarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[685,810,608,634]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Moolgarda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Generic characters described by Whitley such as presence of large pectoral axillary scale, adipose eye fold covering one third of the eye, toothless jaws, terminal upper jaw, moderately thick upper lip and origin of second dorsal and anal fin opposite to each other correlates with 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith 1948" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1948" box="[151,409,716,742]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Valamugil" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,265,716,742]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Valamugil</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, J. L. B." box="[274,409,716,742]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" pagination="833 - 843" refId="ref13518" refString="Smith, J. L. B. (1948) A generic revision of the mugilid fishes of South Africa. Annual Magazine of Natural History, South Africa, 11 (14), 833 - 843." type="journal article" year="1948">Smith 1948</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. He also compared description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cuvier" authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1829" box="[802,1035,716,742]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Mugil" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capito">
<emphasis box="[802,948,716,742]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Mugil capito</emphasis>
Cuvier
</taxonomicName>
, described by Günter’s (1861) as a genotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="D.S.Jordan &amp; J.Swain" authorityYear="1884" box="[289,337,753,778]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Liza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[289,337,753,778]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Liza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and referred to the hidden maxilla in his fish which is also a distinguishing character of 
<emphasis box="[1316,1437,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1948" box="[1316,1433,752,778]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Valamugil" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Valamugil</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson, J. M." box="[151,342,788,814]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" pagination="457 - 562" refId="ref13589" refString="Thomson, J. M. (1997) The Mugilidae of the world. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 41 (3), 457 - 562." type="journal article" year="1997">Thomson (1997)</bibRefCitation>
and Ghasemzadeh (1997) did not accept the Genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1945" box="[954,1079,788,814]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Moolgarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[954,1079,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Moolgarda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and accepted genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1948" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1948" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Valamugil" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1323,1437,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Valamugil</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, J. L. B." box="[151,293,824,850]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" pagination="833 - 843" refId="ref13518" refString="Smith, J. L. B. (1948) A generic revision of the mugilid fishes of South Africa. Annual Magazine of Natural History, South Africa, 11 (14), 833 - 843." type="journal article" year="1948">Smith, 1948</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Senou (2002) recognized the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1945" box="[718,843,824,850]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Moolgarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[718,843,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Moolgarda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1948" box="[1018,1132,824,850]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Valamugil" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1018,1132,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Valamugil</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of it. 
<bibRefCitation author="Durand, J. D. &amp; Chen, W. J. &amp; Shen, K. N. &amp; Fu, C. &amp; Borsa, P." box="[151,386,860,887]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" pagination="73 - 92" refId="ref12096" refString="Durand, J. D., Chen, W. J., Shen, K. N., Fu, C. &amp; Borsa, P. (2012 a) Genus level taxonomic changes implied by the mitochondrial phylogeny of grey mullets (Teleostei: Mugiliformes: Mugilidae) molecular phylogenetic evidence challenges two centuries of morphology- based taxonomic studies. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 64, 73 - 92. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2012.03.006" type="journal article" year="2012">
Durand 
<emphasis box="[244,295,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of molecular studies proposed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1948" box="[941,1055,860,886]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Valamugil" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[941,1055,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Valamugil</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1945" box="[1112,1237,860,886]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Moolgarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1112,1237,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Moolgarda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are polyphyletic. Eschmeyer and Fong (2015) assigned 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1945" box="[580,705,896,922]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Moolgarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[580,705,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Moolgarda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid genus.
</paragraph>
